    • Method Detail

      • calculatePotential

        public double calculatePotential(Chip c,
                                 boolean b)
        Calculates the potential of this 2D field slice.
        Parameters:
        c - the chip for which the potential is calculated
        b - true if a vertical-sequence (along the z-axis) should be considered in the calculations.
        Returns:
        the potential of this field slice

      • potentialTrace

        public double potentialTrace(Chip c,
                             int startX,
                             int startY,
                             int dx,
                             int dy)
        Check if a sequence of the win length is feasible. The easier this is to achieve the larger the potential. The more chips that have to be placed before this sequence can be completed the lower the potential.
        Parameters:
        c - the chip for which a sequence potential is calculated
        startX - the x-coordinate of the first chip in the sequence
        startY - the y-coordinate of the first chip in the sequence
        dx - the x-component of the trace vector
        dy - the y-component of the trace vector
        Returns:
        the potential of this sequence

      • potentialTraceVertical

        public double potentialTraceVertical(Chip c,
                                     int startX,
                                     int startY)
        Check if a vertical sequence of the win length is feasible. The easier this is to achieve the larger the potential. The more chips that have to be placed before this sequence can be completed the lower the potential.
        Parameters:
        c - the chip for which a sequence potential is calculated
        startX - the x-coordinate of the first chip in the sequence
        startY - the y-coordinate of the first chip in the sequence
        Returns:
        the potential of this (vertical) sequence

      • howManyUnderneath

        private int howManyUnderneath(int xPos,
                              int yPos)
        Calculate how many empty spaces (so not occupied by chips of the local player or the opponent) are underneath a certain position in the field slice.
        Parameters:
        xPos - the x-coordinate of the position
        yPos - the y-coordinate of the position
        Returns:
        the number of empty spaces underneath that position

      • inField

        private boolean inField(int x,
                        int y)
        Check if a position is inside the field slice.
        Parameters:
        x - the x-coordinate of the position
        y - the y-coordinate of the position
        Returns:
        true if the position is inside the field, false otherwise.

      • potential

        private double potential(double foundation,
                         double streak)
        Calculate the potential of a possible winning sequence.
        Parameters:
        foundation - the amount of chips needed such that the chips can be actually placed on top of existing chips in the field.
        streak - the amount of chips (belonging to the player for which the potential is calculated) already present in the possible winning sequence
        Returns:
        a floating point number representing the sequence's potential
